      "name": "Operating envelope for VAD hemolysis CFD assessment",
      "description": "The validated operating envelope spans inlet flow rates of 3.0–6.0 L/min (±0.05 L/min measurement uncertainty), impeller rotational speeds of 2400–3200 RPM (±10 RPM), inlet pressure of 5–15 mmHg, outlet pressure of 60–120 mmHg, blood temperature of 36–38 °C, and hematocrit of 35–45%. Geometric fidelity is maintained within ±50 µm of the nominal FDA generic pump geometry. Five canonical operating points (3 L/min / 2400 RPM, 4 L/min / 2600 RPM, 4.5 L/min / 2800 RPM, 5 L/min / 3000 RPM, 6 L/min / 3200 RPM) are explicitly validated against experimental hemolysis index measurements."
    }
